# Post Publishing Pipeline

- Treat `posts.js` as the source of truth for blog cards and order.
- When adding a new post, update `posts.js` first (`slug`, `date`, `title`, `description`).
- Regenerate pages with `python3 scripts/generate.py` after content updates.
- Run `python3 scripts/typograph.py` after generation to normalize typography.
- Keep `sitemap.xml` updated through the generator, do not edit it manually.
- For HTML post files, preserve existing structural blocks (`post-header`, `post-body`, `post-nav`).
- Before commit, verify no accidental deletions in `posts/`, `blog/`, `tags/`, or `_partials/`.
- Tag pages live in `tags/` (e.g. `tags/knigi.html`), partials in `_partials/`.
- Blog entry point is `blog/index.html` (URL: `/blog/`). `blog.html` in root is a redirect stub — do not edit.
